<TITLE> Ribery wants to play for Barca says Van Bommel </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, April 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - France midfielder Franck Ribery wants to move to Barcelona, his Bayern Munich team mate and captain Mark van Bommel has said. "Franck has told me he wants to play for Barcelona. He is the best player in Germany and his style of play would fit well with Barca's because he is strong with great technical ability," Van Bommel, a former Barca player, told Spanish radio station RAC1. Bayern host the Primera Liga leaders in the second leg of their Champions League quarter-final on Tuesday, looking to overturn a 4-0 deficit from last week
